---
title: Herb-Roasted Chicken Dinner with Carrots, Potatoes, and Pecan Cranberry Salad
description: If roasting two chicken halves* sounds like a daunting feat, don’t worry: the prep is simple, and most of the magic really happens in the oven, when it’s getting all crisp and browned and juicy. Nevertheless, you’ll convince your whole family that you’re a force to be reckoned with in the kitchen when you bring that beautiful bird to the table. *Yes, technically, that’s a whole chicken, but we like them already halved and trimmed because that way they cook more evenly.
